Text: It's time for Jeff Bezos to take care of business right here on Earth and pay his fair share in taxes.

I’m pushing for three changes to our tax laws—a #WealthTax, a Real Corporate Profits Tax, and long-term funding for the IRS to go after wealthy tax cheats—to make billionaires & mega-corporations start paying their fair share.

Add your name to join me: https://t.co/XdCf8UDxwx
Jeff Bezos forgot to thank all the hardworking Americans who actually paid taxes to keep this country running while he and Amazon paid nothing. https://t.co/tjOeCWbUA8

This is how we build a future for all of our kids.
https://t.co/TmXiGo02hp

When giant corporations dominate markets, it means higher prices and worse options for consumers, lower wages and less power for employees, and fatter profits for top executives. I’m glad to see President Biden working to level the playing field. https://t.co/pHETcF9kFi

It’s our job in Washington to make sure that Dreamers finally have a pathway to citizenship. America is their home, and they are #HereToStay.

We need to make quality, affordable child care and early learning available for all of our babies—and we need to raise wages for all of our child care workers and preschool teachers, so they can be paid like the professionals they are. I’m in this fight all the way.

The filibuster doesn’t block the GOP’s top priorities: confirming extreme right-wing judges and slashing taxes for the rich. But it gets in the way of Democrats meeting all the needs of the American people, I’m done playing by two sets of rules. #EndTheFilibuster
President Biden must #CancelStudentDebt to start to close the racial wealth gap.

Education is supposed to be a ticket to the middle class. But Black Americans have to borrow more to buy that ticket & often have to get more degrees to deal with a discriminatory job market. So our broken student debt system widens the Black-white wealth gap.

The way I see it, creating jobs has to be about investing in places where we haven’t been investing enough as a nation—like roads, bridges, child care, and defeating the climate crisis. And billionaires and giant corporations must pay a fair share.

Billionaires and giant corporations use every trick in the book to wriggle out of paying to keep our country running. We’ve got to give the IRS the tools they need to crack down on wealthy tax cheats.

Voting is the foundation of our democracy. The filibuster is not.

Republicans across the country are passing law after law after law to make it harder to vote. 

They’re gearing up to gerrymander as many safe GOP seats as possible.

The message is clear: They’re scared to face the will of the people in a free and fair election.

It’s one thing to know in the abstract that the ultra-rich play by a different set of rules.

It’s another thing to have the facts shoved in your face.

Let’s start to level the playing field here with a #WealthTax. https://t.co/oDu7PbRW27
